full_address: the east bank of the Chicago River from Berteau to Pensacola (and a bit beyond)  Chicago 60618
ownership: The land managed by Riverbank Neighbors is located on the traditional unceded homelands of the Council of the Three Fires: the Ojibwe  Odawa  and Potawatomi Nations. Many other tribes such as the Miami  Ho-Chunk  Menominee  Sac  and Fox also called this area home. The region has long been a center for Indigenous people to gather  trade  and maintain kinship ties. Today  one of the largest urban American Indian communities in the United States resides in Chicago. Members of this community continue to contribute to the life of this city and to celebrate their heritage  practice traditions  and care for the land and waterways. Riverbank Neighbors is the management group thru Neighborspace on MWRD property.
